OL,3,CChancellor to squeeze spending
OL,4,Cfollowing growth collapse
OL,6,FEven at the time this looked
OL,7,Foptimistic, or toppy, especially given
OL,8,Fthe shock to business's costs and
OL,9,Fconfidence caused by Rachel Reeves's
OL,10,Fbig rise in employers' national
OL,11,Finsurance.
OL,13,FSince then there has been a bigger
OL,14,Fglobal shock: Trump, and his tariffs.
OL,15,FThe consequence is that every
OL,16,Fprofessional forecaster, from the OECD
OL,17,Fto the US Federal Reserve, is
OL,18,Fdowngrading growth forecasts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
