OL,3,CChancellor to squeeze spending
OL,4,Cfollowing growth collapse
OL,6,FSo everything else being equal, the
OL,7,Fchancellor is set to miss both of her
OL,8,Ffiscal targets, the primary one that
OL,9,Fsays there should be no borrowing to
OL,10,Ffinance day-to-day expenditure and the
OL,11,Fother one that says debt must be
OL,12,Ffalling as a share of GDP or national
OL,13,Fincome.
OL,15,FHer fiscal headroom has evaporated,
OL,16,Fwhich is not something she says she
OL,17,Fwill tolerate. For better or worse,
OL,18,Fher self-defining precept is that her
OL,19,Ffiscal rules must never be breached or
OL,20,Fsoftened.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
