OL,3,CChancellor to squeeze spending
OL,4,Cfollowing growth collapse
OL,6,FWhat will give?
OL,8,FWe already know, as of yesterday, that
OL,9,Fspending on disability benefits will
OL,10,Fbe cut by #5 billion. But she needs
OL,11,Fmore than that to balance the books.
OL,13,FSo the forecast annual rise in public
OL,14,Fservice spending from 2026-2030 of
OL,15,F1.3% will be reduced to nearer 1%.
OL,17,FTo be clear, this is still not
OL,18,Fausterity. These are real rises.
OL,20,FBut for many government services it
OL,21,Fwill feel like austerity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
